        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2169561049" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18131706071309033455">Another homerun Harry Bosch novel. I don&apos;t call this a &quot;guilty pleasure,&quot; as some literati might imagine it to be. <br/><br/>Michael Connelly is the premier writer of literary police procedurals. He&apos;s gotten much better over time. The result is today&apos;s most interesting, flawed and deeply conflicted police protagonist--and his intense, cerebral crime detecting. <br/><br/>In <u>Two Kinds of Truth</u>, the two separate conflicts/crimes involve trafficking and slavery of the elderly and disabled for opioid gathering and distr</span>
  <span id="freeText18131706071309033455" style="display:none">Another homerun Harry Bosch novel. I don't call this a "guilty pleasure," as some literati might imagine it to be. <br /><br />Michael Connelly is the premier writer of literary police procedurals. He's gotten much better over time. The result is today's most interesting, flawed and deeply conflicted police protagonist--and his intense, cerebral crime detecting. <br /><br />In <u>Two Kinds of Truth</u>, the two separate conflicts/crimes involve trafficking and slavery of the elderly and disabled for opioid gathering and distribution and the possible tampering of sealed evidence of rape that could let a rapist go free.<br /><br />Another recommendation if you have the slightest interest in criminal procedurals or police thrillers.</span>
  <a data-text-id="18131706071309033455" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

