    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2061961923" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2061961923" />
    <a title="Skip" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1389748-skip"><img alt="Skip" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1231161516p2/1389748.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2061961923?book_show_action=true">Nov 16, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Skip" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Skip" href="/user/show/1389748-skip">Skip</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1389748-skip?shelf=crime-detective">crime-detective</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2061961923" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7304153224881268415">Excellent addition to the Bosch series, with three stories: a cold case involving a mother who disappeared with an infant at home, presumably murdered by the husband (a case that has bothered the head of Harry&apos;s new chief), a professional hit on two local pharmacists, father and son, who seem to be providing painkillers based on falsified prescriptions, and finally, one of the murderers Harry put away, on death row, petitions for release based on DNA evidence and an accusation that Harry planted</span>
  <span id="freeText7304153224881268415" style="display:none">Excellent addition to the Bosch series, with three stories: a cold case involving a mother who disappeared with an infant at home, presumably murdered by the husband (a case that has bothered the head of Harry's new chief), a professional hit on two local pharmacists, father and son, who seem to be providing painkillers based on falsified prescriptions, and finally, one of the murderers Harry put away, on death row, petitions for release based on DNA evidence and an accusation that Harry planted the key evidence. The latter two stories are almost all of the book, with Harry going undercover, with DEA's blessing, to find the head of the operation and bring the killers to justice. The other story involves Harry, with Mickey Haller's help and investigator, trying to figure out how the DNA match to a dead convict and finding an old mentor to come back from the dead.<br /><br />Connelly's social commentary is always interesting, from the book's title to publicizing the widespread, high-dollar world of prescription drug abuse, where law enforcement is falling down. There are "two kinds of truth in this world. The truth that was the unalterable bedrock of one’s life and mission. And the other, the malleable truth of politicians, charlatans, corrupt lawyers, and their clients, bent and molded to serve whatever purpose is at hand.”</span>
  <a data-text-id="7304153224881268415" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


