<div id="review_2992439234" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2992439234" />
    <a title="Adrienne" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/29830776-adrienne"><img alt="Adrienne" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1528256309p2/29830776.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2992439234?book_show_action=true">Oct 04, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Adrienne" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Adrienne" href="/user/show/29830776-adrienne">Adrienne</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Audible Audio " href="/book/show/35233401-two-kinds-of-truth">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/29830776-adrienne?shelf=thriller">thriller</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/29830776-adrienne?shelf=police-investigations">police-investigations</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2992439234" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8314878582865945248">4.5 actually. I had forgotten what a wonderful writer Michael Connelly is - how he can make a story have so many plausible twists, (with an evident sense of humour at times), how everything makes sense at the end of the story and his prose is great. Principally the Harry Bosch is such a great character. A man who follows his own path and as close to true police procedure as possible. Nevertheless he is aware of his foibles. While always close to the main love of his life, being his daughter.<br/>Unpu</span>
  <span id="freeText8314878582865945248" style="display:none">4.5 actually. I had forgotten what a wonderful writer Michael Connelly is - how he can make a story have so many plausible twists, (with an evident sense of humour at times), how everything makes sense at the end of the story and his prose is great. Principally the Harry Bosch is such a great character. A man who follows his own path and as close to true police procedure as possible. Nevertheless he is aware of his foibles. While always close to the main love of his life, being his daughter.<br />Unputdownable</span>
